00:56:04.220 --> 00:56:09.140
would be the matrix presentation
of p0, which would present

00:56:09.140 --> 00:56:11.450
the effect of this polarizer.

00:56:11.450 --> 00:56:18.740
The p0 will be a matrix
in this form, 1, 0, 0, 0.

00:56:18.740 --> 00:56:25.280
If I have this P0
acting on the z,

00:56:25.280 --> 00:56:29.120
for example, I can have the
p0 acting on the z, then

00:56:29.120 --> 00:56:34.220
basically what would happen
after the light passed

00:56:34.220 --> 00:56:41.960
through this polarizer will
become z multiplied by p0.

00:56:41.960 --> 00:56:47.900
So basically all
this p0 matrix does

00:56:47.900 --> 00:56:56.530
is to extract the position
of the field in the x-axis.

00:56:56.530 --> 00:57:01.130
But I'm just writing it
down in the matrix format.

00:57:01.130 --> 00:57:03.950
And on the other
hand, for example, I

00:57:03.950 --> 00:57:09.850
can have this easy axis,
which is 90 degrees, which

00:57:09.850 --> 00:57:12.920
affects the x-axis, which
is in the y direction,

00:57:12.920 --> 00:57:17.960
then I write this down in
the form of p pi over 2.

00:57:17.960 --> 00:57:23.330
This pi over 2 is the
angle between the easy axis

00:57:23.330 --> 00:57:25.940
and the x direction.

00:57:25.940 --> 00:57:29.250
And in this case, you
are going to get 0, 0, 0,

00:57:29.250 --> 00:57:32.570
1 because all this
matrix set notation

00:57:32.570 --> 00:57:36.440
does is to extract the
component which is actually

00:57:36.440 --> 00:57:38.840
in the y direction.

00:57:38.840 --> 00:57:41.630
And you can of course multiply--

00:57:41.630 --> 00:57:45.440
when you have an incident
electromagnetic wave

00:57:45.440 --> 00:57:50.450
which you can extract the
polarization z matrix, you just

00:57:50.450 --> 00:57:54.770
multiply p pi over 2 and z.

00:57:54.770 --> 00:57:59.270
Basically you can actually
get the resulting polarization

00:57:59.270 --> 00:58:03.080
of the electromagnetic
field after passing

00:58:03.080 --> 00:58:06.530
through this polarizer.

00:58:06.530 --> 00:58:11.000
What is going to happen is
that only the y component

00:58:11.000 --> 00:58:12.110
will survive.

00:58:12.110 --> 00:58:15.820
In the case of easy axis
aligned in the x direction,

00:58:15.820 --> 00:58:20.330
only the x component
will survive.

00:58:20.330 --> 00:58:25.170
So now let me go through
a short example here.

00:58:25.170 --> 00:58:31.010
So suppose initially I have
an electromagnetic field

00:58:31.010 --> 00:58:36.110
polarized, it's linearly
polarized in the y direction.

00:58:36.110 --> 00:58:38.630
And I have that
electromagnetic field

00:58:38.630 --> 00:58:43.130
passing through a polarizer,
which is actually theta

00:58:43.130 --> 00:58:47.000
degree away from the y-axis.

00:58:47.000 --> 00:58:56.240
So what is going to happen is
that all the components which

00:58:56.240 --> 00:58:59.550
is parallel to the axis survive.

00:59:04.890 --> 00:59:09.940
All the projected components
in the axis perpendicular

00:59:09.940 --> 00:59:14.800
to the easy axis didn't make it
because the electrons are going

00:59:14.800 --> 00:59:17.860
to be oscillating up
and down like crazy

00:59:17.860 --> 00:59:21.670
to compensate and then
refract that component.

00:59:21.670 --> 00:59:24.880
So what is going to happen
is that after passing

00:59:24.880 --> 00:59:30.190
through the easy axis, the
direction of the polarization

00:59:30.190 --> 00:59:33.040
will be altered such
that it's actually

00:59:33.040 --> 00:59:38.560
in line with the easy
axis of the polarizer.

00:59:38.560 --> 00:59:40.500
So you can see
that, after passing

00:59:40.500 --> 00:59:45.310
through this polarizer, the
direction of the polarization,

00:59:45.310 --> 00:59:48.940
this is still
linearly polarized,

00:59:48.940 --> 00:59:52.690
the direction is
changed by theta degree.

00:59:52.690 --> 00:59:55.810
And also the
amplitude also changed

00:59:55.810 --> 01:00:00.880
because only the component
parallel to the easy axis

01:00:00.880 --> 01:00:01.770
survived.

01:00:01.770 --> 01:00:07.880
Therefore, the magnitude
of the E vector

01:00:07.880 --> 01:00:13.090
becomes E0 cosine
of cosine theta.

01:00:13.090 --> 01:00:17.550
And therefore, the amplitude
of the light got reduced.

01:00:17.550 --> 01:00:21.190
It becomes I0
cosine theta squared

01:00:21.190 --> 01:00:24.460
because the intensity
of the light

01:00:24.460 --> 01:00:28.660
is proportional to E squared.

01:00:28.660 --> 01:00:33.070
So after all this, this
